article.headline: Northwestern St. 83, Centenary 76
article.story: NATCHITOCHES, La. (AP) -- Northwestern State saw five players hit double figures, led by Keenan Jones' 20 points, as the Demons defeated Centenary 83-76 Tuesday night. Jone was 10-of-13 from the free-throw line and 5-of-6 from the field. Jermaine Wallace added 15 points, Jermaine Spencer and Clifton Lee had 11 each and Colby Bargeman had 10 for the Demons (3-2). Lee also pulled down eight rebounds. Chad Maclies led the Gents (0-3) with 23 points and 13 rebounds. Tyrone Hamilton added 14 points and Jarmorrow Moragne had 10 to go along with eight assists. Northwestern St. led 40-31 at the half.
